OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FThe NFER study ` which explores
OL,8,Finterviews with staff and pupils from
OL,9,Fnine secondary schools and survey
OL,10,Fresponses from more than 600 secondary
OL,11,Fschool teachers and leaders ` found
OL,12,Fpupils in sanctions-led schools were
OL,13,Fmore likely to perceive attendance
OL,14,Fpolicies as "punitive and unfair".
OL,16,FIt said schools that combined reward
OL,17,Fwith sanctions had seen "higher pupil
OL,18,Fengagement" with attendance policies
OL,19,Fas children felt motivated to attend.
