OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FEarlier this month, Pepe Di'Iasio,
OL,8,Fgeneral secretary of the Association
OL,9,Fof School and College Leaders (ASCL),
OL,10,Fsaid school had become "optional" for
OL,11,Fsome families since the Covid-19
OL,12,Fpandemic and he suggested that the
OL,13,F"blunt instrument" of fines for
OL,14,Funauthorised absences was not
OL,15,Freversing the trend.
OL,17,FThe former Conservative government
OL,18,Fannounced plans to raise fines for
OL,19,Fpupil absences in February last year,
OL,20,Fto boost attendance since the pandemic.
