OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FIn September, school absence fines in
OL,8,FEngland rose from #60 to #80, and a
OL,9,Fparent who receives a second fine for
OL,10,Fthe same child within a three-year
OL,11,Fperiod will now receive a #160 fine.
OL,13,FThe NFER study suggests that illness,
OL,14,Fmental health issues and term-time
OL,15,Fholidays were primary reasons for
OL,16,Fpupil absence in the participating
OL,17,Fschools.
