OL,5,Creport
OL,7,FMr Di'Iasio said: "We agree that a one-
OL,8,Fsize-fits-all approach is not the way
OL,9,Fforward, and school leaders must be
OL,10,Ffree to tailor policies to the needs
OL,11,Fand characteristics of their cohort.
OL,13,F"Appropriate rewards and sanctions
OL,14,Fhave their part to play, but
OL,15,Findividualised support that quickly
OL,16,Fidentifies why a pupil is absent from
OL,17,Fschool, and helps them to return to
OL,18,Fthe classroom as soon as possible, can
OL,19,Fbe hugely effective."
